This paper is about image super-resolution using deep neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the design of the neural network architecture, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the usage of GPU memory, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and the optimization of the network, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE).
